description:
The Spring Equnox ‚Äì half day, half night, reminds us of the importance of balance, something hard to find in these times of dramatic imbalance.  Spring also reminds us of the huge growth-energy that pours forth from the womb of Mother Earth bringing new life, new promise, new possibilities.  It calls each of us to look inward at what we want to grow in our lives, our families, our communities, our world.  What seeds do we want to plant to be empowered. May the Turning of the Seasonal Wheel from Winter to Spring and the Rebirth of Life bring us deeper attunement to the wisdom that lives in the blossoming flowers, the blooming fruit trees, the intelligence of cyclic seasons older than our measurements of human time on this planet.
May the Coming of Spring renew our hope in the dark moments of despair, fear, violence and negativity, that love, that light, that kindness, that generousity, that dignity, that caring, that daring to dream of a healthy, peaceful, just and sustainable world, along with the willingness to work for it, could actually be realized if enough of humanity unites hearts and minds to reach a critical mass for transformation.
Each thought, each feeling, each action, goes out as an energy into the planetary field of consciousness influencecing what  happens in the world.
May this Spring help us move from thought forms based on separation towards those that recognize and honor the underlying unity of all life on this precious, amazing and beautiful Mother Earth.
May we open our hearts and minds to the creative miracle that life is and our potential to co-create with the Creator of this Universe. #springequinox #renewal #rebirth #meditation #ascension üôèüå∫

description:
"Never Lose Your Sense of Wonder"

It happens we lose it when we get caught up in this routine called¬†life,¬†we lose ourselves. We lose our sense of importance for recognizing the beauty around us, and our inner lust for adventure that lies somewhere deep within us all.
.
. 
If you happen to be stuck in this routine called life, which we all experience from time to time, my suggestion for you would be to stand up for yourself and break this cycle! Search for the life that you have always dreamed of the life you've always wanted to live. .
.
Whether it‚Äôs for two days, two weeks, or if you‚Äôre lucky, two months, you should buy that plane ticket for the destination that has always been on your bucket list and put this routine called life on hold.
.
.
I did it and let me tell you 2018 was the best year of my life I've learned to appreciate everything that I have, bring a new perspective on life and always have open eyes and ears to the world! . .
.
landing in a new countries brings out that childlike curiosity in us all.
You will find yourself pointing at iconic structures that you thought you would only come across in magazines. You may stumble across an old beaten-path that leads to the most breathtaking fields of lavender or a breathetaking Scandinavian beachfront!
.
. 
guys go out and explore, break the chains of what we consider "life" and live a little, I truly believe travel is the recipe for reinvention!
. 
So go out there and explore!
.
.
.

description:
"One has to get wet,
To dance in the rain."
-Me
.
"Farmers who wait for perfect weather never plant.
If they watch every cloud, they never harvest."
-Solomon 11:4
.
.
If we try and wait for everything to be perfect, we can miss many great things in life.
I know I've missed good stock options, deals on equipment, date opportunities, and just fun times.
.
.
Being nomadic helps us to evaluate what's important and not miss as many opportunities. So, sometimes we work during a storm, go to the Drive-In movies in the rain, or even sneak in to grab a quick photo when we see a cool spot off the road.
.
As with anything, finding out what the consequences of missing out are, helps you to dance in the rain.
.
What's something that you've danced in the rain about lately?
.
.
..
.
P.S. I would highly recommend checking out this location in North Carolina , Just Us Orchard.
We are currently in Selmer TN
.

description:
Baby Ivy is just as much an answer to Ellanor‚Äôs prayer as to mine. She has wanted a baby sister for literal YEARS. She used to have multiple make believe sisters. üòÇ She was so excited when I got pregnant, claiming it was a girl, and she was devastated when we lost the baby.
‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä
‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî
‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä
I remember trying to sugar coat telling her. Trying to avoid saying the real words. After all, she was only 4. She was ‚Äútoo little‚Äù to understand. I had to literally say ‚Äúthe baby died‚Äù In order for her to understand, because she wasn‚Äôt too little, my perception of her was. It was heartbreaking to watch her grieve what she believed to be her sister she had been so longing for. üòî
‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä
‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî
‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä
While I was recovering one night, Ellanor got out the broom and dustpan and was sweeping the whole house. She said, ‚ÄúI‚Äôm cleaning for you because I know it makes you happy and you‚Äôre sad about our baby that died, so I want to make you happy!‚Äù üò≠
‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä
‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî
‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä
Her emotional capacity is absolutely astounding and Her compassion is so inspiring. She loves so deeply. Serving and giving are two of her biggest love languages. For as difficult as she can be, there are so many more ways she is absolutely amazing. I am so thankful that she is my first baby, and the absolute best big sister, and leader of our smith family band kids üò≠üòç I love that she constantly speaks of Ivy as her dream come true, and she loves her so much she just wants to bite her! Saaaaaaame, girl. Same. üß°

description:
It's a wrap!!
.
Yesterday marked the bitter-sweet end to the recce part of my prep for SW100. I've enjoyed heading out to Wales for jam-packed weekends of trying to cover as much ground as I could, without going too far off my training plan. On my solo recce adventures, I carried all my kit for the weekend, running from point to point! The hills have been brutal, the downhills have been fun, I've had sun, rain, graupel, gale force winds and -12C wind chill. I've seen so many places I'd not even heard of, and met so many lovely people.
.
I spent a total of 6 days trying to recce this route, and yet I only covered 90% of it. It still blows my mind (and sends me on a mild meltdown) that I would be attempting to do this in under 40 hours.
.
I've learned what I could from my micro adventures, marked my map where I went off-piste, and willed myself uphill when my mind and body struggled (all the hills).
.
My recce is done.
.
#sw100 #100miletraining #recce #running

description: on this mental health awareness day in the year of our dark lord 2018 i simply can‚Äôt come up with a coherent ramble to speak on my own experience, and instead of fighting that- i‚Äôm giving in to the fact that it‚Äôs okay to not be okay (something i‚Äôm doing a lot these days). been wading through a lot this year, thanks for sticking around. SO i‚Äôm going to repost what i managed to slap together last year: ‚Äòhappy mental health awareness day! if you know me irl you know that my mental health is real bad + i have spent the last several years trying to not suppress or hide that! i switch from jokes n chuckles to directly addressing how nice not existing sounds within mere seconds! i feel so deeply + have to remind myself every day that empathy is not a weakness! i know it's not fun to hear this, but it's real! it's my reality, + so many other ppl's realities too! we all should chat about this more! talking about these things should be as common place as talking about the cold going around the office! if you ever want a listening ear- i am here for you! today i'm not doing well in that darn brain + the fact that i can say this publicly is wonderful n (mostly) absolutely terrifying all at once! thx for reading this! now i'm gonna go try not to let my anxiety + depression eat me today!‚Äô

description:
Are you willing to sacrifice who you are for what you want to become?
‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä
I won't lie to you, more than once in life I've felt like I've arrived. Owning my own business, staff working for me, respect from people I've never met, etc etc etc #IfYouKnowYouKnow ‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä
But it wasn't enough. ‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä
It either didn't last or I intentionally blow it up. I was comfortable and I convinced myself I didn't have to keep pushing... but in my heart, I knew there was still more, so I started over, again and again. ‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä
Sacrifice = an act of giving up something valued for the sake of something else regarded as more important or worthy. ‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä
I've NEVER seen success work without sacrifice. Its just one of those universal laws, you can either use it to your advantage or you suffer consequences of violating it.
‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä
Only you know what you need to sacrifice in your life to accomplish your goals. Money, comfort, sleep, relationships, "clout", time, the list is infinite and its different for each of us. But what I can tell you is it will cost you, you just need to decide if its worth it.
‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä
My advice, don't leave this life with regrets. Neither because you didn't give it your all or because you sacrificed too much in the process. Find the balance. That's what #PracticalDreaming is really about. ‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä
I know it's not easy, but trust me, you got this. ‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä

description:
'LOOTING CULTURE: CURATING ABSENCE' by Martina Contento (@martinacontento), fourth year diploma project. ‚†Ä
‚†Ä
Unveiling has been the main curatorial strategy which guided me throughout both my research, 'Looting Culture: Curating Absence, Interstitial Spaces for Art During WWII from Europe to Argentina,' and my proposal for Lars M√ºller's Nomadic Book Store, 'Wall of Curiosities'.‚†Ä
‚†Ä
‚ÄòLooting Culture: Curating Absence‚Äô is a reflection on censored narratives throughout WWII as a critique to current museum strategies. This research explores the extreme and unconventional environments artworks inhabited during WWII, a history otherwise systematically omitted by museums. Covered are spaces of occupation and evacuation; the remote, extreme and unconventional spaces that artworks inhabited during World War II, both in the protective enclosures of the oppressed, and in the appropriation sites of the oppressors. It examines the way artworks changed the remote landscapes they inhabited. ‚†Ä
‚†Ä
In hiding precious artwork collections from the designated SS organisations, gallery dealers and institutions in both Germany and occupied zones dispersed their collections to the most remote landscapes and extreme environments in Europe. These environments included grand countryside Chateaus, false apartment rooms, bank vaults and underground bunkers in isolated locations. The oppressors similarly appropriated distinctive environments to house the hundreds of thousands of stolen artworks. Their appropriation sites comprised of German castles and war monuments, abandoned trains, remote rock caves, and salt-mines. ‚†Ä
‚†Ä
This research brings to the foreground these undocumented intermissions by tracing the trajectories of 4 artworks, and documenting the ways in which these artworks altered their inhabited landscapes.‚†Ä
‚†Ä
2016-17‚†Ä
Diploma 15, Museum Lab, with Giulia Foscari (@giuliafoscariwr), Ekaterina Golovatyuk (@ekaville), Harikleia Karamali (@harikleia_kar).‚†Ä

description:
POSITIVE BODY IMAGE DISCUSSION SESSION

I am happy to announce that on Sunday 26 March, from 3-5pm, @moretoyoga and I will be leading an open discussion on the subject of yoga and body image at @fold.london

We will explore the relationship between the practice of yoga and our perceptions of our own bodies. We will dive into the history and philosophy of how yogis, several thousand years ago, related to their physical bodies as well as how they considered deeper ‚Äúsheaths‚Äù such as emotional and energetic bodies. This historical background offers a foundation for considering the more contemporary issues modern yogis face, especially in the age of social media. Our aim is to create an open, supportive discussion to talk about body image and the ways yoga can impact one's body image and self-esteem, both positively and negatively. The session will comprise both discussion and practical exercises, including meditation and mantra creation; however, we will not practice any yoga asana. ¬£20 donation. All money raised will be donated to Stem4 charity, which supports young people struggling with mental illness, including eating disorders (stem4.org.uk)

Book your spot: http://www.fold-london.co.uk/events-1/

#yoga #londonyoga #bodyimage #positivebodyimage #yogateacher #yogaeverydamnday #yogaeverywhere #yogaforeverybody #fundraiser #charity #mentalhealth #eastlondon #newingtongreen #bopo #selflove #meditation

description:
Along with Tactical Rifles we cover the standard Bolt-Action Rifle on the course. The first Bolt-Action Rifle was produced in 1824 by Johann Nikolaus von Dreyse. They are still used today, commonly for hunting and snipers as they are adequate to deliver a single lethal shot from a safe distance.

For those still reading and like the details... The Bolt action is a type of firearm action where the handling of cartridges into and out of the weapon's barrel chamber is operated by manually manipulating the bolt directly via a handle, which is most commonly placed on the right-hand side of the weapon (as most users are right-handed). When the handle is operated, the bolt is unlocked from the receiver and pulled back to open the breech, allowing the spent cartridge case to be extracted and ejected, the firing pin within the bolt is cocked (either on opening or closing of the bolt depending on the gun design) and engages the sear, then upon the bolt being pushed back a new cartridge (if available) is loaded into the chamber, and finally the breech is closed tight by the bolt locking against the receiver.

description:
PLEASE READ AND SHARE WITH ALL PARENTS OF CHILDREN YOU KNOW. THANK YOU. 
The Doctors and Nurses at Chelsea West hospital have asked if we will share photos of Alba to educate about vaccinations. 
Posting these heartbreaking images of our beautiful baby girl who contracted MEASLES is extremely difficult, we are still in hospital 8 days after being admitted. 
She was too young for her MMR vaccination when she got sick which meant she has had to fight this killer virus with no immunity. 
Measles is not ‚Äújust a rash‚Äù it can cause blindness, encephalitis and pneumonia.
We need to do more people. Get your children vaccinated.
The MMR does not cause life threatening issues like Measles does. Your babies might feel under the weather for a day or so but believe me you‚Äôd accept that over what we have been through.
It has been absolutely horrific watching our daughter fight this with her eyes swollen shut for 4 days. She has been in the dark, scared with a high fever that lasted for over two weeks. In hospital she has been scanned, X-rayed poked prodded bloods taken, lumbar punctures done, canulars fitted, swabs taken, ECG Eccos, obs done every 20 mins, tube fed, on a drip, oxygen, pumped full of drugs, anti inflammatory pain relief antibiotics you name it she‚Äôs had it. The truth is this all could have been prevented if the protection layer of older kids above Alba had been vaccinated.
Educate yourselves, talk about it, spread the word SHARE THIS POST. Do whatever you need to do because without the care of Chelsea and west Doctors our beautiful baby would not be here today. #mmrvaccine #measles #getvaccinated #healthprotection #educate #pleaseshare

description:
NOTTINGHAM:
I was so excited to see @chaiiwala open in Nottingham, we really needed it!
¬∞
To eat we ordered a Butter Chicken Roti and Masala Chips. These were both cute little snacks. The butter chicken was good but we felt like it could have done with a bit more sauce. The masala chips were faultless - a must try in our eyes if you're visiting @chaiiwala !
¬∞
To drink: Karak Coffee (of course), Iced Karak Coffee and Rose Falooda. The karak coffee and iced karak coffee both hit the spot, one of my favourite things to get from Chaiiwala. The falooda flavour was banging, but personally I would like to see more of the little bits in the drink because that's why I get falooda! There was a decent amount and tbh there can never be enough so maybe I'm being really picky!
¬∞
Overall, we love Chaiiwala and this Nottingham branch has lived up to the brand and its high standards. Congrats to @chaiiwala for their continued expansion and we wish them nothing but huge success inshaAllah!
¬∞
All pictures are taken and owned by us so please tag us/give credit if you would like to use them.

description:
I love hats and all, but I‚Äôm not sure if I can pull this one off üòÇ. I often think of how complex we are as human beings. We have the capability to feel a wide spectrum of emotions and feelings. I can be dead serious one moment but later on have the capability to die of laughter. I‚Äôm definitely goal oriented and focused, but I never take myself too seriously to be honest (if you‚Äôve ever met me üòâ). I can laugh at myself almost daily. I think it‚Äôs important for my own #mentalhealth to do so. Otherwise, I get caught up in absolute-type thinking. You know the kind where everything is black and white. Good or bad. All or nothing. Sure there are times when I get caught up and forget to lighten up, and it might take another person (or sometimes animal) to snap you out of it. description:
BE HUMBLE OR BE HUMBLED
.
If there‚Äôs an activity in the world more humbling than running, I have yet to come across it!
.
A couple of days ago, I had a run where I seemingly had everything going against me but I got it done and was satisfied with my pace and actually felt GREAT afterward!
.
Fast forward to today. I hydrated and ate well throughout the day. I was totally fired up to get the run in! But for reasons that I have yet to figure out, the run was an absolute struggle almost from the beginning. I felt decent for the first minute or two, but that changed pretty quickly. I felt like I was moving OK, but the GPS was telling me something different. .
Looking back, I gotta admit I was feeling myself a bit after Monday‚Äôs run. I figured if I felt so good after I overcame a few obstacles I would absolutely crush the next run with no problem!
.
It was almost as if God was reminding me that I‚Äôm not as far along in my training as I like to think I am. .
Fair enough!
.
Lesson for the day: be humble or you will be humbled!
.

description:
We explored Doubtless Bay (or rather Karikari Peninsula). We stopped at Matauri Bay, Coopers Beach and Matai Bay and these were all stunning beaches! 
We found an old plastic shoe insole and a plastic toy washed up on Coopers Bay. It's crazy to think that humans, even in first world countries, are not controlling their waste and things like this end up in the oceans, on the beaches and even in the foodchain (not only human food)! Everyone knows that humans need to consume less and, in first world countries especially, this has to be a top priority. Capitalism and consumerism have ruined this amazing planet and will unfortunately continue to do so.

#doyourbitfortheenvironment

description: "Rimettiamo la Chiesa al centro del Ristorante....." Carissimi Ristoratori , vi sento spesso criticare l'Istituto  Alberghiero senza mai esserci stati dentro, io lavoro da 20 anni esatti nella scuola e MAI MAI e poi MAI  nessuno del settore mi ha chiesto di venire a capire come funziona il dietro le quinte, come se un cliente vi criticasse il vostro Ristorante senza mai esserci stati, sono sicuramente che vi incazzereste a morte! Ma tanti di voi sostenete che i ragazzi non sono all'altezza e non sono come una volta, forse √®  tutto giusto , ma la soluzione come mai non la tirate fuori ? Ve lo dico io perch√© non sapete di cosa parlate, e allora vi do qualche dato ( indiscutibile ) - Prima si facevano 18 ore a settimana di laboratorio contro le 6 di adesso - Prima avevamo materie prime a non finire contro una bottiglia di vino ogni 30 alunni- l'attrezzatura ne avevamo da vendere ora √® meglio che non ve lo dico. Ma a voi che vi frega? molto pi√π facile dire che gli alunni sono svogliati....! Pensate le squadre di calcio hanno i vivai e ci investono....voi quando vi affacciate e venite a darci qualche idea vincente ? Poi nella scuola, ci sono dei colleghi che non hanno mai lavorato e non insegnano il minimo sindacale, ma prima di parlare e farci la cojonella venite a sporcarvi le mani....e aiutateci a Rimettere la chiesa al centro del Ristorante!!! description: You can get rid of a square jaw line &bruxism and achieve sharper chin at once ü§ó A case of severe hypertrophy of the masseter muscle because of bruxismüò¨Teeth Grinding ( Bruxism ) If you have bruxism, you may unconsciously clench your teeth during the day, or clench or grind them at night. Bruxism is a common problem; reports of prevalence range from 8‚Äì31% in the general population. Several symptoms are commonly associated with bruxism, including; headaches, facial muscle pain, earache, tightness and stiffness in the shoulders, pain and stiffness in the jaw joint and surrounding muscles (known as the temporomandibular joint area). Besides hypertrophy of the masseter muscle, which may lead to the appearance of a severe square jaw, is another side effect of bruxism. Treatments with Botulinum Toxin Type A, can provide tremendous relief from jaw soreness, headaches, and other unpleasant problems associated with Bruxism. Treatments for Bruxism can also soften the appearance of the jaw line. Botulinum Toxin Type A injection ( just 3-4 times for a year ) is an excellent treatment for patients who are bruxist or grinding their teeth besides option for shrinking the masseter muscles to slim the jawline. #smile #teeth #bruxism #cosmetics #esthetics #botulinum #botox #jawline #bruxism #masseterbotox #lips #happy #aesthetic #art #face #dentist #jawline #slimmingworld #dentista #uk #london #harleystreet #laserdentistry #dentalimplant #zirconia #emax #veneers

description: Only 2 weeks left of Anthea Hamilton: The Prude, her first show in both London spaces at @thomasdanegallery | ü¶ãüåºü¶ãüåº. .\nFor the prude, modesty becomes extreme. The prude will not permit themselves, or others, sensuous enjoyment in life. Hamilton's interest in the literary figure of "the prude" in part, references Cecil Vyse ‚Äî the aloof character of E.M Forster's A Room with a View (1908). Perceiving himself a sensitive intellectual, Vyse in reality, remains detached from lived experience. This obstinate self-awareness is matched by a cultivated, exaggerated style. This skewed mode of being, the prude-as-persona, serves a framework for the exhibition, where the prude is put to use as a proxy for Hamilton, who performs a "hands off" physicality.

Over the next month we‚Äôd like to take the time to highlight our Structural Engineering and Design capabilities.

Our experience providing detailed design for clients covers a wide range of greenfield and brownfield projects. 
Examples include detail design of Living Quarters (LQ), equipment change out, support grillages, repair clamps, riser and j-tube installation, caisson replacement, equipment supports and ROV launch systems. 
Our experienced design team is capable of producing detailed engineering drawings on AutoCAD 2-D & 3-D to tight schedules with the necessary quality control applied. The detail design is supported by a full suite of analysis capabilities for both fixed and floating structures.

description:
NATURE IMMERSION: there is growing evidence to support a direct link between our mental health and wellbeing and our connection to nature.
.
For many of us our lifestyles are far removed from the natural world.
.
Bristol is a unique place for many reasons but the opportunity to visit authentic slices of nature dotted around the city is a real blessing but not everyone has this opportunity.
.
Our public parks are often very sterile places full of clipped grass and scattered trees. By altering our approach to our public parks and even our own gardens we can begin to reconnect to a natural world we are inherently a part of
.
The younger we start the better!
.

description: This picture depicts a German Sd.Kfz. 164 Panzerjager Nashorn of Schwere Panzerjager Abteilung 655  on the Eastern Front,1943. 1943 was the major turning point for the Germans and axis in Europe during WW2, with Axis held Africa having fallen, The Italian succession in September, and the failure of the Germans to win in the battle of Kursk. The Germans thus started a major fighting retreat on the Eastern Front, never to mount another major assault, reinforced the Italian front with German troops so as to block the allied advance, and started to reinforce the Atlantic Wall defenses in preparation of any allied attempt at landing there. (Which we all know would happen in June of 1944.) I will give the Germans credit though, as their retreat in the East was very well done, and inflicted very many Soviet casualties. The Soviets had so many men though, that this barely hurt them. This Nashorn has tick (tally) marks on its main gun, signifying how many enemy tanks it took down, which seems to be quite a few. This just again shows the consequence the Germans had of opening two fronts in the war. If the USSR was never invaded, the majority of German troops, which fought there, could have been used in the West in Italy and later France. Maybe the Soviets would have even fought along side the Germans like in 1939. Who knows how things might have turned out, but it sure would have played out differently. #War #history #vintage #retro #rustic #usa #america #england #france #germany #italy #russia #japan #boat #tank #batlle #worldwar2 #worldwarii #ww2 #wwii #worldwar2foryou Also go follow @the_ww2_memoirs @world.war.europe @ww2_history9 @world_war_2_militaria @_world_war_2_pictures @militaryhistory @ww2_german_history and @ww2dailyhistory

description:
Where do you go to achieve quiet time?

Do you allow yourself quiet time? Or do you enable other people to intrude, to take up this time? 
Many busy women, especially those with small children, tell me its impossible to have their own time - even for 10 minutes.

A few minutes is all it takes to start each day well. 
Could you set your alarm to be up 20 minutes earlier than usual? Time to brew tea or coffee, and sit in peace with your thoughts before the rest of the family are awake?

Give yourself permission and agency to start your day with peace and self-reflection.

This one took me by surprise, I didn‚Äôt expect to love it. I‚Äôll be honest, I only picked it up as it was a library hold that I couldn‚Äôt renew any further but I finished it in two days, it was fast paced and thought provoking and very almost the perfect thriller. At 14 years old Jack is left in charge of his two younger sisters after his pregnant mother went missing three years prior. She left them on the hard shoulder of the motorway to get help, and never returned. Jack spends his evenings breaking into empty houses and stealing what he can to keep his family going. That‚Äôs how he discovers the knife. .
.
.
The books has alternating chapters following Jack, DCI Marvel and Catherine While, this really helps getting to know the characters and each reveal hidden depths. Jacks story is gut wrenching but then a chapter with Marvel would have me grinning, it‚Äôs was an emotional rollercoaster! Overall it was a unique and clever story with surprise reveals along the way, if your a thriller fan and haven‚Äôt read this one yet I couldn‚Äôt recommend it enough! .

description:
Written 6/27/18 ‚ÄùYou are always so positive and happy! ‚ÄúYou spread good energy around you‚Äù ‚ÄúYou are such a nice friend, sister, child and student‚Äù 
These are the sort of things I‚Äôve been told my whole life, and it‚Äôs has been the truth, but not the whole truth. Because what happens to the happy girl when she all of a sudden doesn‚Äôt feel as happy? To always be the good girl is pretty exhausting, always doing the right thing and what is expected from you. Especially when In reality you are sad, mad, confused and disappointed. It‚Äôs been downs and ups and downs again, but I have realized that you can‚Äôt please everyone. Some will only see themselves and it has nothing to do with you or your achievements! But I can honestly say that I‚Äôve never felt better than I do right now, right now my physical and mental health is in sync and I feel better than ever. When you finally get rid of the dark cloud of thunder that is blocking the way, that‚Äôs when you can shine. I know who I am and my values that no one can take away from me, I know that I have real friends that makes me feel like I‚Äôve won the friendship lottery, to care not because you have to but just because you want to is the most beautiful thing I could ever imagine. And I got an amazing family that is my A team!
I am so grateful for this but if you‚Äôve gotten this far, see this as your daily reminder to not judge someone based on only what you see from the outside, every person has their own story and it‚Äôs worth being listened to.

Last but not least, @ my one personal cloud of thunder, this is me not giving a fuck about you! I know you miss me, I would miss me too

You're everywhere. 
At the parks I frequent.

Even when I understood, 
That we were so pernicious together.

As someone who is not using their degree directly and whose resume represents climbing a jungle gym (vs climbing a corporate ladder), you would think I would have been anticipating a change in the direction of my business.‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä
.‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä

.‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä
Truth is, I wasn't. So it surprised me when I had that moment. At first it was like WTF?!?!? And now it was more ...ohhhh..hmmmm...that makes sense (Sorta. I think. Lol).‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä
.‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä

.‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä
I don't want to give away too much yet, but all I will say is that I'm stepping away from the consulting and workshops, as well as blogging about blogging.‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä
.‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä

.‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä
Which is so hard (AND SCARY) because I've worked so hard to brand my business that way. It meant saying no to a lot of things that I normally would have said yes to.‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä
.‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä
.‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä
But I needed a change. And all the things that were/weren't happening were confirming this.‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä
.‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä
.‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä
.‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä
As Makinthebacon goes through the rebrand (currently in the planning/researching stage because these things don't happen overnight and can take time), I will continue to focus on my other endeavours: The Defining Digital Moment with @gbrpublishing, planning the next event for the @Kaibiganconnection and interviewing more people for the @baconbitsnbytes podcast.‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä
.‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä

.‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä
I should probably put my site "under construction/doing renos" mode soon. But I wanted to tell you here first.‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä
.‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä

description:
when life gives you lemons üçã 
as much as I like to think I‚Äôm okay with change, I forget how hard it can be sometimes. There‚Äôs been a lot of change in my life the past few months, and it has become quite overbearing all of a sudden. Lately, I‚Äôve been struggling to breathe. Speak. Move. See. The past week I have been mindlessly shovelling food into my mouth until I feel physical pain, avoiding my feelings and feeling my waistline expand as a result. I use food as a way to self harm, when I‚Äôm too afraid to allow room for my soul to grow instead. Maybe it‚Äôs time to stop pushing my negative emotions down until they inevitably overspill, leaving me to drown in a flood of fears & worries. I need to find the courage to open myself up to all my emotions, the good and the ‚Äúbad‚Äù. To remember: It is okay to feel. It is okay to hurt, to be vulnerable, imperfect. There is no shame in this.

Today, on the 11th hour of the 11/11/11 I vow to accept, release and move forwards. Time to be whole again.

description:
During my Talent/national costume round of Mrs India Uk I showcased the national costume of Bihar. A historic and holy state of India. 
This post owes a major thanks to this amazing friend of mine without whom I would not have been able to showcase this saree!  @abhishek6nov! Abhi THANK YOU for allll the effort you gone through to get me this saree allll the way from madhubani! Totally Adore you and fully love you for this! üòäü§ó The saree I showcased is very unique, 
It‚Äôs tussar bhagalpuri silk with madhubani art on it. Weighs almost nothing and feels like a baking paper!  India is the exclusive producer of tussar Bhagalpuri silk. madhubani paintings are unique as it is done with fingers, twigs, brushes, nib-pens, and matchsticks, etc. Using natural dyes and pigments, and is characterised by eye-catching geometrical patterns. The theme of painting is based on natural elements such as sun, moon , stars, peacocks, turtle, fish, bamboo trees etc. 
All these Patterns and themes symbolise love, valour, devotion,prosperity&fertility. 
The pallu of this saree that I am wearing here, showcases a man and women getting married. This is to depict Ram and Sita‚Äôs marriage ceremony! 
According to Hindu mythology this art dates back about 2500 years ago. when the king of Mithila, Raja Janak asked an artist to capture his daughter Princess sita‚Äôs wedding with Prince Ram through this art form. Hence the art is also known as Mithila art! 
Proud to have my roots connected to Bihar!

Great to catch-up with gorgeous friends @katrinastrick and Natasha at the launch of On Violence. Rather than feeling helpless about what to do about our national crisis, please buy and read #OnViolence. @mupublishing The book focuses on prevention strategies in the form of education and culture change.
You can do something. Whether it be in your conversations with your children, your family, your community, on the sporting field or at work.
Buy copies for your bookclub, your colleagues, your local library.
The booküìö proceeds will go to Our Watch. @ourwatch 
At her booklaunch Natasha ran through the dispiriting statistics: on average one woman dies violently every week, usually at the hands of someone she knows; domestic violence costs the economy $2.1 billion a year; it is the single biggest contributor to injury, death and disability for women aged 15-44; one in four women has experienced some form of violence by age 15; and every two minutes the police are called out to a domestic violence incident.

description: Outtake from the Rt 66 road trip I'm on with @statefarm and @savingplaces for @natgeo.\nI‚Äôve reached the halfway point of a 30-day, 2,278 mile road trip down historic Route 66 with The National Trust For Historic Preservation and author Megan K. Stack @megkstack76. \nHere are her words about this journey. ‚ÄúWe‚Äôre traveling the Mother Road all the way west from Chicago to Santa Monica this month, swinging through hardscrabble towns and booming cities; past tourist traps and national monuments and every imaginable roadside kitsch rendered in neon. Perhaps none of the passing icons can rival Route 66 itself, the pavement muse to John Steinbeck and Jack Kerouac, retracing the journey of desperate Okies and Prohibition-era gangsters and the 1950s holiday makers of a newly mobile America. Nowadays the famed highway comes and goes in spurts, having been rerouted, eclipsed by the interstates and finally allowed to sink into disrepair. But the fascination with Route 66 endures. A new generation of tourists from around the planet still make the pilgrimage along the quirky, poignant and uniquely American roadway. From diners and drive-ins to thriving state parks and ordinary families, the road offers a rich portrait of what America has been, and what it may yet become.‚Äù //Route 66 is the most celebrated stretch of highway in America. However, with more travelers opting for the interstate, it needs our help. Join @savingplaces in our journey across America‚Äôs most iconic roadway at natgeo.com/route-66.

I just can‚Äôt even describe how it felt seeing the amount of rubbish that was picked up and pulled out by divers in the ocean today. I am the first to put my hand up and say I haven‚Äôt done enough in the past but hand on heart, while staring at those precious little people I love with every inch of my body, I promise to now make a conscious effort to do more. I 100% believe - monkey see monkey do! I can‚Äôt even say thankyou enough to @seashepherdadelaide for all their hard work putting this clean together and thankyou so much for letting us be apart of it. description:
YOGA + SOUND BATH ‚òÄÔ∏è .

Happening next Friday at @triyogauk in Shoreditch. Join the wonderful yoga teacher Ellie @eleonora.ramsby.herrera and myself for a two-hour sound bath and yoga immersion. We hope to see you there! ‚òÄÔ∏è
.
The theme of our sound-poetry workshop this month follows the element of earth. We will explore how the symbolism of the element earth can represent a certain type of intention and metaphor that serves to ground your energy and concentration and help you cultivate a stable and rooted support and focus through the work of your legs, feet and the ground you stand on. ‚òÄÔ∏è
.
The yoga class will explore developing an aware connection to the muscles and joints of your feet as well as using the legs as a strong foundation in a variety of traditional standing yoga asanas such as warrior B, warrior C, chair-and tree pose. 
Gravity will be of central importance as we work with the placement- shifting- and giving of weight through our bones as we root into the ground to then grow tall from the base of support, rising up through spine and crown.

description: Our 1st night out as parents was Dec 2015, just 3 months after she was born - around our wedding anniversary and days before my now estranged Father said ‚ÄúI do‚Äù for the 2nd time. It was the textbook disaster of a meal for 1st time parents. But that paled into total insignificance when we went to bed, hardly speaking, to be woken less than an hour later by terrifying coughing. She was struggling to breathe as we ran into the nursery with her, NHS Direct already on the phone. And so began a ridiculous number of A&E and out of hours visits. The winter that followed was dark. So dark. There was a particularly bleak week in February where I honestly didn‚Äôt think I could go on. The sleeping in shifts night on night to keep her upright to prevent the coughing took its toll. The cradling her in my arms during the day, the anxiety she‚Äôd never have the energy to sit up like her little friends were doing chipped away at every inch of my soul. It was not the maternity leave I had dreamed of. Finally, finally we were listened to and the consultant referral came through (the consultant we needed, doesn‚Äôt see patients privately) just after her 1st birthday - Sep. There were lie awake at night retests for life limiting diseases and handfuls of chest x rays. In the end, we said good bye to the chronic bronchiolitis (which had morphed into an untreated bacterial infection that was taking over her lungs) thanks to a pretty straightforward antibiotics protocol. And here we are... the most positive consultant appointment to date. We‚Äôre probably 1 more appointment away from discharge (although we‚Äôll miss him üò¢ and be forever grateful to him) providing we can make it through next Winter. We went to this park, right beside the hospital, following the appointment today and she went up & down this slide so many times. She is limited by so little & attacks life with sometimes terrifying amounts of energy. I guess I wanted this to be a post of hope, a little celebration, an acknowledgement of the utter crippling rawness of first time parenting when you hit a bump in the road. Hold on tight, shout for help, the sunny days, they are a coming, even when it's only darkness at your door üòòüòòüòò

„Éª„Éª„Éª
Ryan Gander is featured in this year's iteration of The Armory Show's Platform section. Curated by Sally Tallant, executive director of the Queens Museum and former director of the Liverpool Biennial. Titled 'Worlds of Tomorrow' the section will draw its inspiration from the 1939 New York World‚Äôs Fair and relate that event to today‚Äôs current political climate.

In 1918, Belgian abstract sculptor and painter and founding member of the De Stijl group, George Vantongerloo created Komposition Aus Dem Ovoid (Composition from the ovoid). Over a hundred years later, British artist Ryan Gander comically revisits this artwork with Het Spel (My neotonic ovoid contribution to Modernism) (2019), an enlarged and swollen form made of up of ovoids covered in multi-colored artificial fur balls.

Visit the installation, and The Armory Show from 7-10 March at Piers 92 & 94

description:
This past Sunday brought us the highly anticipated premiere of our very own @krljackson short film ‚ÄúRelapse‚Äù, created by both himself and the brilliant @ambreenrazia ~

In his own words... ‚ÄúA young father returns home from prison with the prospect of rebuilding his life and his relationship with his daughter. To anyone who feels like they are trying but feel progress is stagnant, slow or hopeless. Your are not alone! It‚Äôs so easy to pay attention to all that‚Äôs happening and compare yourself to it all. Let it all go! Everyone‚Äôs journey is one of trials and tribulation don‚Äôt be fooled by your screens. Be patient with yourself, for your adventure will be like no other! Have the courage to get up and try again, cultivate that inner voice that tells you your great! Making this film has been the biggest challenge in my career thus far but by far the most worth while. For the two days we shot this film I was that boy in the playground once again. Thank you to all who have joined us on this journey and @ambreenrazia for your support, insight and incredible spirit. The film is now headed for the festival circuit before an online release. Will keep you posted.‚Äù

description: So what‚Äôs going well for you right now? What do you love? What are you looking forward to? Ask someone today anyone of these questions instead of just a ‚Äúso how are you‚Äù and watch the difference in engagement, depth and connection. Watch how your connection with others, and ultimately your ability to connect better with yourself increases your sense of meaning and purpose just by asking others simple questions like these on a daily basis. Be it a stranger, colleague or loved one, your capacity to not only love but allow yourself to be loved will increase tenfold by this simple little habit... description:

.
All things alive vibrate. Allow yourself to be immersed in the healing sounds and vibrations of sacred gongs, Himalayan singing bowls, Native American flutes, percussion, and other world instruments. Experience the deepest level of relaxation, clearing the mind and body of negativities that cause pain, anxiety, and dis-ease. Realign and harmonize yourself to a state of inner peace and connectedness. As we participants lie down, we set our intentions and let the vibrations of the sacred sounds help us access our inner wisdom. Wear comfortable clothes.
.
Rev. Laksmi Scalise, RYT 500, IYM, began a Yoga practice more than 40 years ago. She is involved with the healing arts as a sound healer, gong master, Reiki master, dowser, and astrologer. Laksmi studies under and assists Grand Gong Master Don Conreaux. She is a chakra-balancing practitioner at the Integral Yoga Wellness Spa.
.
Lois Harrison is a healing sound practitioner, a nationally certified massage therapist, and universal healing Tao instructor. She has played the flute since the age of 12 and utilized sound frequencies during her own healing journey. In 2008 Lois became a certified sound practitioner at the New York Open Center‚Äôs Sound and Music Institute, has studied with Gong Master Don Conreaux and other leading sound healers, and has led workshops and sound journeys throughout the United States and England. She continues to share her experiences passionately with others through private practice, events, and workshops.
.

WE NEED YOUR HELP! Well it seems we have run into a bit of trouble here in Harps towers. With all the excitement of getting ready for our the world premiere of our new show at The Above The Stag Theatre in Vauxhall ( Friday 17th May, 10PM)

It seems we have been served a copyright infringement with our band name. There is a Greek woman with a band called 'The Harps' also. Its a Rock Metal band and they don't seem to have any harps either! So since we don't wanna get sued, just like U2 (previously The Hype), Westlife (previously Westside), The BeeGees (previously The Rattlesnakes), Snowpatrol (previously PolarBears) & Liberty X (previously Liberty) were gonna have to change our name. 
We want your best suggestions and we are going to announce our new name at our gig! The best suggestion will win 2 tickets to our show so get your thinking caps on! We also still have a few tickets left, so if you would like to come and support us get booked asap! 
Tickets available now ¬£12

https://abovethestag.ticketsolve.com/shows/873605902

Much Love 
The Harps Boys xxx

I believe we need to accept that we‚Äôre building something here just as City had their project and Chelsea had theirs. The difference is we‚Äôre doing it without funds. Thats what‚Äôs makes it more difficult, that‚Äôs what makes it take time. But it‚Äôs also what makes it Tottenham. I wouldn‚Äôt swop our squad, manager and chairman for a financial doped up club. Honestly wouldn‚Äôt. To buy and cheat your way to success (both those clubs where targeted out by football leaks with evidence of breaking rules) and not be ashamed tells you exactly what kind of clubs they are and supporters they have. I want a trophy, but I don‚Äôt need a Carabao Cup one. I think if we continue our process, trophies will come, bigger ones than the Carabao. Sometimes we get caught up in the media‚Äôs demands for us to win a trophy as proof of that we‚Äôre good enough. Allow the carabaos and the FAs. This is a very practical course with lectures and hands on using pigs jaws and surgical models.

Full details can be found here:

www.idealdentalcourses.co.uk/oral-surgery-masterclass-for-general-practitioners/

This course was over subscribed when we ran it in January so book early to avoid disappointment.

You can register your interest or book on by e-mail Emma:
ehulley@roselanedentalpractice.co.uk

This is what one of the delegates said about the last course:
"The course was great. Chris was a great. Happy to discuss subjects off topic too. For example conversation evolved to socket preservation. Within minutes we had photos of the technique. Great depth and knowledge of oral surgery. All questions and queries answered thoroughly.
I felt privileged to have such a small working group. Couldn‚Äôt have asked for a nicer bunch to spend the few days with.
There are no other courses like this. It was perfect for me. Updating skills gained from an SHO post 10 years ago.
Felt like lots of time given to hands on. Which was perfect. " #oralsurgery #dentalcourses #postgraduatelearning #idealdentalcourses #practicallearning
